{
  "buggy_files": ["drivers/net/wireless/intel/iwlwifi/pcie/drv.c"],
  "buggy_functions": ["iwl_dev_info_table"],
  "confidence": 0.95,
  "reasoning": "The iwl_dev_info_table at lines 978-997 is missing PCI subdevice entries for 0x2526 device ID. Specifically, subdevice IDs 0x4010, 0x4018, and 0x401C are not present in the table. When the driver probes a device with one of these subdevice IDs (via iwl_pci_probe at lines 1031-1042), the lookup loop cannot find a matching entry in iwl_dev_info_table, causing the device to fall back to a generic configuration instead of getting the proper iwl9560_2ac_160_cfg configuration with 160 MHz capability. This results in firmware not being loaded correctly. The missing entries should be added to the table for device 0x2526 with these subdevice IDs using the iwl9560_2ac_160_cfg configuration (like the existing 0x4030 entry at line 995)."
}

